            "arabicMeaning": "محفظة نقود",
            "synonyms": [
                "billfold (American)",
                "purse (for men—British)"
            ],
            "example": [
                {
                    "text": "He patted his back pocket in panic when he realized he'd left his "
                },
                {
                    "text": "wallet",
                    "colorize": true
                },
                {
                    "text": " at the restaurant"
                }
            ],
            "tips": "Men typically carry wallets in pockets; women often carry purses/handbags (which may contain a smaller wallet inside). NOT the same as 'purse' in American English (which means handbag)."
        },
        {
            "word": "garbage",
            "wordType": "noun",
            "definition": [
                {
                    "text": "Unwanted waste material that is "
                },
                {
                    "text": "thrown away",
                    "highlight": true
                },
                {
                    "text": "; "
                },
                {
                    "text": "rubbish or trash",
                    "highlight2": true
                }
            ],
            "arabicMeaning": "قمامة / نفايات",
            "synonyms": [
                "trash (American)",
                "rubbish (British)",
                "waste"
            ],
            "example": [
                {
                    "text": "Don't forget to take the kitchen "
                },
                {
                    "text": "garbage",
                    "colorize": true
                },
                {
                    "text": " outside before it starts to smell in the heat"
                }
            ],
            "tips": "American English prefers 'garbage' or 'trash'; British English uses 'rubbish'. 'Litter' = garbage carelessly dropped in public places (not in bins)."
        },
        {
            "word": "rush",
            "wordType": "verb",
            "definition": [
                {
                    "text": "To move or act with "
                },
                {
                    "text": "great speed and urgency",
                    "highlight": true
                },
                {
                    "text": ", often without "
                },
                {
                    "text": "careful thought",
                    "highlight2": true
                }
            ],
            "arabicMeaning": "يَهرع / يَعْجَل",
            "synonyms": [
                "hurry",
                "dash",
                "race"
            ],
            "example": [
                {
                    "text": "She had to "
                },
                {
                    "text": "rush",
                    "colorize": true
                },
                {
                    "text": " to catch the last train home after her meeting ran late"
                }
            ],
            "tips": "Often implies careless haste that leads to mistakes ('He rushed his homework and made many errors'). Noun form: a rush (sudden movement) or rush hour (busy traffic time)."
        },
        {
            "word": "realize",
            "wordType": "verb",
            "definition": [
                {
                    "text": "To become fully aware of something suddenly; to "
                },
                {
                    "text": "understand a fact",
                    "highlight": true
                },
                {
                    "text": " or "
                },
                {
                    "text": "situation clearly",
                    "highlight2": true
                },
                {
                    "text": " for the first time"
                }
            ],
            "arabicMeaning": "يُدرك / يتفطّن",
            "synonyms": [
                "become aware of",
                "recognize",
                "understand suddenly"
            ],
            "example": [
                {
                    "text": "Halfway through his speech, he suddenly "
                },
                {
                    "text": "realized",
                    "colorize": true
                },
                {
                    "text": " he was reading from the wrong notes"
                }
            ],
            "tips": "American spelling: realize. British spelling: realise. NOT 'realize' meaning 'make real' (that's a different, rare meaning). Common error: 'I didn't realize' (correct) vs. 'I didn't realized' (incorrect)."
        },
